{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:45:39.846475+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 14e35346190d0ff04ea56d634a34dbac593ed1c9)", "id": "lc_15684c56-647a-48ca-8239-f87285ed93b5"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"name\": \"vue3-vite-starter-template\",\n  \"description\": \"Vue.js 3 Vite starter template with Pinia, Vue Router, Bootstrap and more.\",\n  \"version\": \"0.0.0-semantic-release\",\n  \"license\": \"MIT\",\n  \"repository\": \"https://github.com/kouts/vue3-vite-starter-template\",\n  \"packageManager\": \"pnpm@10.20.0\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"preinstall\": \"npx only-allow pnpm\",\n    \"dev\": \"vite\",\n    \"build\": \"vite build\",\n    \"preview\": \"vite preview\",\n    \"build-preview\": \"vite build && vite preview\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint \\\"**/*.{vue,ts,js}\\\"\",\n    \"lint-fix\": \"eslint --fix \\\"**/*.{vue,ts,js}\\\"\",\n    \"test:unit\": \"vitest\",\n    \"test:unit-coverage\": \"vitest run --coverage\",\n    \"prepare\": \"husky\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"bootstrap\": \"^5.3.8\",\n    \"jsdom\": \"^27.1.0\",\n    \"pinia\": \"^3.0.3\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^4.0.6\",\n    \"vue\": \"^3.5.22\",\n    \"vue-router\": \"^4.6.3\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@commitlint/cli\": \"^20.1.0\",\n    \"@commitlint/config-conventional\": \"^20.0.0\",\n    \"@fullhuman/postcss-purgecss\": \"^7.0.2\",\n    \"@fullhuman/vue-cli-plugin-purgecss\": \"^7.0.2\",\n    \"@kouts/eslint-config\": \"^3.0.9\",\n    \"@vitejs/plugin-vue\": \"^6.0.1\",\n    \"@vue/compiler-sfc\": \"^3.5.22\",\n    \"@vue/test-utils\": \"^2.4.6\",\n    \"autoprefixer\": \"^10.4.21\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^9.39.0\",\n    \"husky\": \"^9.1.7\",\n    \"lint-staged\": \"^16.2.6\",\n    \"prettier\": \"^3.6.2\",\n    \"sass\": \"^1.93.3\",\n    \"vite\": \"^7.1.12\",\n    \"vite-plugin-html\": \"^3.2.2\"\n  }\n}", "id": "lc_bdfd73a2-e8dc-4138-a9c4-717071766b0a"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "fbaed76a-3a6c-4331-aa34-dbeb59e6546f", "tool_call_id": "call_518dad08cf4644e39598db67", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:45:50.378450+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the repository evidence, **pnpm is required and npm is not acceptable**. Here's the justification:\n\n---\n\n## Evidence\n\n### 1. `package.json` — `preinstall` script enforces pnpm\n\n```json\n\"preinstall\": \"npx only-allow pnpm\",\n```\n\nThis script runs automatically before any `npm install` or `pnpm install` call. The [`only-allow`](https://github.com/nicolo-ribaudo/only-allow) utility checks the package manager being used and **throws an error if it is not pnpm**. This is an explicit, hard-enforced guard — running `npm install` will fail with an error message telling you to use pnpm instead.\n\n### 2. `package.json` — `packageManager` field\n\n```json\n\"packageManager\": \"pnpm@10.20.0\"\n```\n\nThis field (from the [Corepack](https://nodejs.org/api/corepack.html) specification) declares the exact expected package manager and version. Corepack-aware Node.js environments will automatically use pnpm 10.20.0 for this project.\n\n### 3. `pnpm-lock.yaml` is present\n\nThe repository commits a `pnpm-lock.yaml` lockfile (207 KB). There is no `package-lock.json` (npm) or `yarn.lock`. Running `npm install` would generate a different lockfile, potentially causing dependency resolution inconsistencies.\n\n### 4. `README.md` — documentation uses pnpm\n\nAll commands in the README use `pnpm`:\n\n```\npnpm install\npnpm run dev\npnpm run build\npnpm run test:unit\npnpm run lint\n```\n\nThe only exception is the last entry (`npm run lint-fix`), which appears to be an oversight/inconsistency — but the runtime `preinstall` hook would still block npm for install operations.\n\n---\n\n## Conclusion\n\nContributors **must use pnpm**. The `preinstall` script (`only-allow pnpm`) actively prevents using npm (or yarn) for dependency installation, and the lockfile, `packageManager` field, and documentation all consistently point to pnpm as the expected toolchain.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 509, "prompt_tokens": 5330, "total_tokens": 5839, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 41, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 4608, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0007734888, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0003306588, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00044283}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780962340-iRXKFxBNymCSPSF5D98b", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9a0-ac07-7ff2-8f22-e22825133b18-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 5330, "output_tokens": 509, "total_tokens": 5839, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 4608}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 41}}}}]}}}
